main_4217157\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gem1687246686722.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gem1687246686722.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gem1687246686722.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gem1687246686722\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">User Key Definitions</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"gem1687246686722__topic_d64523e1_d64524e1_d64525e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gem1687246686722__p_d64526e1_d64527e1_d64528e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">UserKeySequence</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">^USER_KEY</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">$CharCharacter</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">TerminationCharacter</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gem1687246686722__section_z1c_cqs_vyb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d780036e67\"> Arguments </h2>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"gem1687246686722__ul_zh5_2qs_vyb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gem1687246686722__li_d28043e1_d28044e1_d28045e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">UserKeySequence</var>—character sequence\n\t\t\t\t\t\tthat initiates the user key.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gem1687246686722__li_d28046e1_d28047e1_d28048e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">^USER_KEY</code>—identifies the sequence in\n\t\t\t\t\t\tthe first column as a user key. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gem1687246686722__li_d28049e1_d28050e1_d28051e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">$CharCharacter</var>—character to be put in the\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$char</span> ProcScript function, making the user key\n\t\t\t\t\t\tavailable for use in the userKey trigger. This allows you to distinguish\n\t\t\t\t\t\tbetween different user keys. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gem1687246686722__li_d28052e1_d28053e1_d28054e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">TerminationCharacter</var>—character that terminates the user\n\t\t\t\t\t\tkey sequence. All the characters that the user enters between\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<var class=\"keyword varname\">UserKeySequence</var> and\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<var class=\"keyword varname\">TerminationCharacter</var> are put in\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$result</span>, making them available for use in the userKey\n\t\t\t\t\t\ttrigger. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gem1687246686722__section_ynf_fqs_vyb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d780036e113\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gem1687246686722__p_d64535e1_d64536e1_d64537e1\">When Uniface encounters user key sequences in the\n\t\t\t\tevent input queue, the userKey trigger (at component level or application level, or\n\t\t\t\tboth) is activated. The values put in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$char</span> and\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$result</span> can be used in the ProcScript in the userKey\n\t\t\t\ttrigger.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gem1687246686722__p_d64538e1_d64539e1_d64540e1\">Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$char</span> makes it possible\n\t\t\t\tto define different character sequences for a <code class=\"ph codeph\">^USER_KEY</code>. The\n\t\t\t\tcharacter code made available in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$char</span> can be used to indicate\n\t\t\t\twhich character sequence was used to activate the userKey trigger.</p>\n</section>\n<div class=\"example\" id=\"gem1687246686722__example_jx1_mqs_vyb\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gem1687246686722__p_d64541e1_d64542e1_d64543e1\">Consider the following definition:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"gem1687246686722__pre_lcw_mqs_vyb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^esc^lL ^USER_KEY^065^009\n^esc^zZ ^USER_KEY^066^009</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gem1687246686722__p_d64544e1_d64545e1_d64546e1\">In this example:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"gem1687246686722__ul_mcw_mqs_vyb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gem1687246686722__li_d28055e1_d28056e1_d28057e1\">Escape L and Escape Z are identified as user\n\t\t\t\t\tkeys, which activate the structure editor function ^USER_KEY. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gem1687246686722__li_d28058e1_d28059e1_d28060e1\">Escape L puts ^065 in\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$char</span>. Escape Z puts ^066 in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$char</span>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gem1687246686722__li_d28061e1_d28062e1_d28063e1\">^009, the Tab character is the termination\n\t\t\t\t\tcharacter. All the characters that the user enters between the beginning of the\n\t\t\t\t\tuser key sequence (Escape L, for example) and the terminator (Tab, for example)\n\t\t\t\t\tare put in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$result</span>. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/niy1665702606431.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger userKey</a><p>Trigger for responding to user-defined key sequences as defined in the Keyboard Translation Table (KTT) or defined in the usys.ini section named as userkeys.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ncx1686824523526.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$result</a><p>Return the result of certain ProcScript commands and tree widget events.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/apo1686824392132.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$char</a><p>In a Unifield, return the Uniface character code for the key that activated a trigger.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4217157\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4217157\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "User Key Definitions Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 User Key Definitions UserKeySequence ^USER_KEY $CharCharacter TerminationCharacter Arguments UserKeySequence —character sequence that initiates the user key. ^USER_KEY —identifies the sequence in the first column as a user key. $CharCharacter —character to be put in the $char ProcScript function, making the user key available for use in the userKey trigger. This allows you to distinguish between different user keys. TerminationCharacter —character that terminates the user key sequence. All the characters that the user enters between UserKeySequence and TerminationCharacter are put in $result , making them available for use in the userKey trigger. Description When Uniface encounters user key sequences in the event input queue, the userKey trigger (at component level or application level, or both) is activated. The values put in $char and $result can be used in the ProcScript in the userKey trigger. Setting $char makes it possible to define different character sequences for a ^USER_KEY . The character code made available in $char can be used to indicate which character sequence was used to activate the userKey trigger. Consider the following definition: ^esc^lL ^USER_KEY^065^009 ^esc^zZ ^USER_KEY^066^009 Copy In this example: Escape L and Escape Z are identified as user keys, which activate the structure editor function ^USER_KEY. Escape L puts ^065 in $char . Escape Z puts ^066 in $char . ^009, the Tab character is the termination character. All the characters that the user enters between the beginning of the user key sequence (Escape L, for example) and the terminator (Tab, for example) are put in $result . Related Links trigger userKey Trigger for responding to user-defined key sequences as defined in the Keyboard Translation Table (KTT) or defined in the usys.ini section named as userkeys. $result Return the result of certain ProcScript commands and tree widget events. $char In a Unifield, return the Uniface character code for the key that activated a trigger. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}